Because we are way past Y2K, into the future, and it's about time we stop using boring 80x25 and 16 colours terminals

The programs or config files to be put here are tested as much as possible, which means "it works for me." Usually this means it works on a Linux machine, in a tmux session accessed from PuTTY. For configuring your terminals to display 256 colours, see the guides already available.
